<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD568071903107AF992" box="[338,615,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Hemipenthes lepidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has similar wing pigmentation to that of 
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56D291903133CF9F8" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56D29190316F1F992" box="[1148,1260,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus">H. albus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56DAF1903176DF992" box="[1274,1392,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scylla">H. scylla</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56C2B1903133CF9F8" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="translucens">H. translucens</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56831195913EFF9F8" box="[356,498,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56831195913F3F9F8" box="[356,494,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="webberi">H. webberi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The cell 
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56B311959106EF9F8" box="[612,627,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">a</emphasis>
is hyaline, the margin of color sinuous and the color limited to the base and anterior margin of the wing. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56B0F197610C3F921" box="[602,734,1643,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidota">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56B0F197610C3F921" box="[602,734,1643,1668]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. lepidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is apparently related with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56D4F19761662F921" box="[1050,1151,1643,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inops">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56D4F19761662F921" box="[1050,1151,1643,1668]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. inops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The broad black scales in the hind tibiae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD568D1198C13F5F90F" box="[388,488,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inops">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD568D1198C13F5F90F" box="[388,488,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. inops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD56B74198C10BBF90F" box="[545,678,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidota">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD56B74198C10BBF90F" box="[545,678,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. lepidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be homologous structures. The genitalia of this species has a medial extension in the epiphallus longer and slender than those in other species, a unique characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD569C219C21307F95D" box="[151,282,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidota">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD569C219C21307F95D" box="[151,282,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. lepidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7613FFD5687D19C213B1F95D" box="[296,428,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidota">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7613FFD5687D19C213B1F95D" box="[296,428,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. lepidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported to have territorial behavior (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8FD29C7613FFD56A9B19C216E7F95C" author="Avalos-Hernandez" box="[974,1274,1759,1785]" pageId="28" pageNumber="48" refString="Avalos-Hernandez, O. (2007) Bombyliidae (Insecta: Diptera) de Quilamula en el area de reserva Sierra de Huautla, Morelos, Mexico. Acta Zoologica Mexicana (n. s.), 23, 139 - 169." type="journal article" year="2007">
Ávalos-Hernández, 
<number id="3DD6BD4A7613FFD56DEF19C216E7F95C" box="[1210,1274,1759,1785]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species has a widespread distribution along all 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD7613FFD56B34181810A6F8BA" box="[609,699,1797,1823]" name="Mexico" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and the West half of the 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD7613FFD56AB518181602F8BA" box="[992,1055,1797,1823]" name="United States of America" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">USA</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
